b) Trade/ Exotic/ Commodities Focus
•
@ostium
:
@arbitrum
perp DEX that embraces RWAs (indices, FX, commodities and event markets). Dual-vault liquidity and an imbalance score keep spreads honest
•
@qfex
: 24/7 perps on US stocks, indices, FX, commodities
• Extended (fka X10):
@Starknet
-settled CLOB with orders such as TWAP, scaled ladders, OCO by default.
@PragmaOracle
(TradFi) +
@StorkOracle
(crypto) oracles, staged liqs, insurance, ADL
•
@grvt_io
:
@zksync
-stack exchange that combines CLOB perps with a privacy-preserving L2. The long game: options, spot, RWAs, unified margin; composable, but private by default
•
@variational_io
(Omni): RFQ, not order-book; vertically integrated market maker (OLP) quotes; zero trading fees; spread P&L flows to the OLP vault and depositors
Risks
• Regulatory relaxations: The arb window can close. Jurisdictions can blur the line between “DEX” and “venue”
• CEXes launching their own perp DEX: claw back market share from the current players while still contributing to the exchange’s bottom line
*Note: excluded the likes of dYdX, GMX and Orderly to focus on relatively new and upcoming Perp DEXes

